<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman Asks Belgium's Claes for EU Support </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tudjman Asks Belgium's Claes for EU Support </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305192494 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1730 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman yesterday sent a 
letter to Willy Claes, Belgian deputy prime minister and foreign 
minister. The message, conveyed by Janko Vranicani-Dobrinovic, 
Croatian ambassador to the Benelux countries, requests Belgium, 
as one of the members of the European Union's [EU] troika, to 
enlist EU support for Croatia's development, which would speed 
up the democratization process and help to gradually resolve the 
problem of Croatian territories under UN protection. 
  Minister Claes and Ambassador Vranicani-Dobrinovic also 
discussed the implementation of the Washington agreements 
between the Croats and the Bosnian Muslims. 
  The Croatian ambassador underlined Croatia's interest in 
concluding an agreement on trade and economic cooperation, 
protection of foreign investments, and double taxation. 
Vrnicani-Dobrinovic requested that Belgium ease or abolish 
visas for Croatian citizens and resolve the problem of workers 
employed by Croatian companies in Belgium. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

