<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Currency To Be Introduced 30 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Currency To Be Introduced 30 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305180494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305180494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Croatian dinar's days are numbered. Croatia 
will be introducing its own currency on Statehood Day, 30 May. 
As you already know, this will be the kuna. The dinar will 
remain legal tender until 7 June, but converting it into the new 
currency will be possible until the end of the year. This was 
revealed to reporters this afternoon by National Bank Governor 
Pero Jurkovic. [passage omitted] 
  The replacement of the Croatian dinar by the new currency of 
the Republic of Croatia will be realized by knocking off three 
zeros, according to National Bank Deputy Governor Zdravko Rogic. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

