<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Continuing Strikes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Continuing Strikes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Oleksy Assails Solidarity's Objectives </H4>

<F P=102> LD0405110994 Warsaw TVP Television First Program Network in 
Polish 1000 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw TVP Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Relayed by Warsaw TV Polonia Network] </F>
  [Text] Sejm Speaker Jozef Oleksy said at a meeting with 
workers at the Warsaw FSO [Automobile Factory] today that, by 
organizing strikes, Solidarity is not fighting in the interest 
of employees but is seeking to achieve the upper hand over other 
trade unions. According to the speaker, Solidarity has been 
deliberately avoiding negotiations with the government. It has 
announced the escalation of strike action because the aim of the 
union is to overthrow Waldemar Pawlak's Cabinet. 
  Jozef Oleksy said that trade unions should primarily fight 
to 
resolve problems of employees and not play political games for 
their own benefit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

