<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Probably thanks to Mr. Akashi's visit, the chetniks 
have reduced the number of cease-fire violations in Sarajevo 
today. Still, their snipers have managed to wound one civilian 
today near the Simon Bolivar primary school in Dobrinja. They 
also fired with an antiaircraft machine gun from Azici on the 
city's free territory. Throughout the day they have been 
carrying out tactical regrouping of men and equipment in various 
directions, and grouping of their army on certain positions 
around Sarajevo. There are indications that their sniper fire 
and other military activities could intensify, so the citizens 
are reminded to take seriously all the caution warnings. 
  This is reported by the [Bosnia-Herzegovina Army] 1st Corps 
Information Center. 

