Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0405113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After an infernal day yesterday, in the evening the 
aggressor continued barbarously shelling civilian populated 
places in the free Zvornik territory until late last night. 
Kovacevici and Vitinica were shelled with T-55 tanks from 
Androvici, Sapna was shelled with 120-mm mortars from Kiseljak, 
and houses were destroyed in Godus with a 205-mm howitzer from 
the direction of Celopek. A multiple rocket launcher operated 
at the Medjedja region from the direction of Kiseljak launching 
projectiles of huge destructive power. Five civilians, 
including three children less than 10 years old, were wounded as 
a result of this special chetnik shelling. 
  Our defense positions were also exposed to constant fire 
from 
all kinds of weapons and artillery pieces. In the morning, the 
shelling with the most destructive long-range artillery pieces 
continued, but despite this, defense lines have remained firm 
and unchanged. 
  This was a report by the Information Service of the 206th 
Chivalrous Brigade of Zvornik for the Radio and Television of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

