<H3> <TI>   TANJUG Reports Muslims, Croats Firing on Serbs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TANJUG Reports Muslims, Croats Firing on Serbs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305220294 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2003 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0305220294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Serb Village Dzindici Under Strong Moslem Fire" -- TANJUG </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Bileca, May 3 (TANJUG) -- Moslem forces in Bosnia on 
Tuesday [3 May] opened strong fire on Serb combatants positions 
in the village of [word indistinct] by the Dzindici, eight km 
southwest of Gorazde, it was announced by the commander of the 
army of the Bosnian Serb republic [passage indistinct] 
  In a simultaneous action, a Moslem unit tried to row across 
the Drina to its right bank but was forced back by Serb forces. 
The regular Army of Croatia went into action for a second time 
in the past four days on the Trebinje battlefront when, from the 
occupied village of Zavale, it attacked Serb positions in Mareva 
Ljuta. The Serb side did not respond, it was announced. Moslem 
forces launched provocations in the upper reaches of the Neretva 
around the locality of Konjic, opening anti-aircraft gun [word 
indistinct] sniper fire on Serb positions in this section of the 
battlefront, but there were no consequences for the combatants 
of the Herzegovina Corps. 
  In the Doboj region, Moslem forces continued their offensive 
and provocative combat actions aimed against Serb positions. In 
addition to intensified small-arms fire along the contact line, 
Moslem forces acted most fiercely from the direction of Bejici 
whence they fired 82-mm mortars sporadically on Serb positions 
west of Doboj. 

</TEXT>

