<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Greets Israel-PLO Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Greets Israel-PLO Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405124394 Sofia BTA in English 1220 GMT 4 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0405124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, May 4 (BTA) -- The Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs of the Republic of Bulgaria states the following in 
connection with the signing of the agreement on limited 
Palestinian self-rule: 
  The agreement signed on May 4, 1994 by Israeli Prime 
Minister 
Yitzhaq Rabin and PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat is an important step 
towards achieving just, all-embracing and lasting peace in the 
Middle East. In a relatively brief period of time after the 
Middle East peace process was launched in Madrid in late 1991, 
two of the most important participants in the negotiations have 
shown that political will, mutual compromises and concessions 
can result in considerable progress in the further solution of 
the complicated problems which have accumulated in the region 
over the past decades. 
  Hailing the signing of this important document, the Republic 
of Bulgaria expresses its belief that it reveals real 
possibilities for continuing peace negotiations after the Madrid 
formula and creates the necessary preconditions for the signing 
of agreements between Israel and the other Arab countries taking 
part in the peace process, preserving and guaranteeing the 
balance of interests of all Middle East states, the declaration 
of the Bulgarian Foreign Ministry reads. 

</TEXT>

