<H3> <TI>   Miners Continue Absentee Strikes 3 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Miners Continue Absentee Strikes 3 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305191694 Warsaw PAP in English 1846 GMT 3 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0305191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, May 3 -- Strikes at 16 coal and 3 zinc and 
lead mines were continuing on Tuesday. The strikes are 
"absentee" strikes which means the miners are not at their 
places of work. 
  The chairmen of Solidarity factory committees in the mines 
and power stations met on Tuesday evening to discuss the forms 
further strike action would take. According to one of the union 
representatives who wished to remain anonymous Solidarity will 
be escalating the strikes in mining. The source said a decision 
to this effect would be taken on Wednesday during a meeting of 
the Slasko-Dabrowski regional Solidarity leadership in Katowice. 
  The strike at Poland's lignite (brown coal) mines was 
suspended on Saturday. Power stations are not limiting 
electricity supplies. 

</TEXT>

