<H3> <TI>   Union Leader Criticizes Government, Strikers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Union Leader Criticizes Government, Strikers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305195994 Warsaw PAP in English 1918 GMT 3 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0305195994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Katowice, May 3 -- Freedom Union leader Tadeusz 
Mazowiecki said during a Tuesday press conference in Katowice 
that the cause of the present tensions in Poland is the "policy 
of procrastination of the government, which has not taken up its 
own standpoint in light of many problems." He added that the 
"political echos of the present strike wave are not subject to 
doubt." According to Mazowiecki the "way to resolve the present 
problems in the country is to clearly define the standpoint of 
the government towards the most important national economic and 
social affairs." 
  When speaking about the strike wave, the Freedom Union 
leader 
said that he wonders why "those who now say that they are 
striking in the name of Solidarity in support of the state 
enterprise pact not so long ago undermined a government which 
created the pact." According to Mazowiecki, "it is unjust that 
all of society suffer due to a strike staged by a narrow social 
group such as that of the coal miners in Belchatow." 

</TEXT>

