<H3> <TI>   Government Approves Agriculture Regulation Fund </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Approves Agriculture Regulation Fund </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405074194 Prague CTK in English 1954 GMT 3 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0405074194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, May 3 (CTK) -- The government at 
today's session approved the proposal for a modification of the 
Market Regulation Fund in Agriculture, Agriculture Minister 
Pavel Koncos said at a press conference today. The fund should 
be financed by a 50 percent share from proceeds from 
privatization of agricultural companies and should start 
operating in June. 
  It will be administered through the National Bank of 
Slovakia 
by some of the banks that have granted loans to agricultural 
producers in the past. Koncos said Polnobanka (Agricultural 
Bank) and Vseobecna uverova banka (General Credit Bank) were 
under consideration. The fund is to provide money particularly 
for technological equipment for agricultural, forest and water 
management companies. 
  Koncos also said the ministry was working on food 
legislation 
which includes stricter criteria for inspecting the quality of 
food products, in line with European Union regulations. He said 
that Slovakia, in contrast to the Czech Republic, had already 
adopted a number of norms corresponding to regulations in the 
General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade, which had also brought 
about the introduction of certificates on imported food products. 

</TEXT>

