<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denmark's Petersen Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Denmark's Petersen Arrives on Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0305171894 Prague CTK in English 1552 GMT 3 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0305171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, May 3 (CTK) -- Denmark supports the 
European Union's expansion by Central and East European 
countries, Danish Foreign Minister Niels Helveg Petersen said 
after his talks with his Slovak counterpart Eduard Kukan today. 
Petersen, who arrived for a two-day visit to Slovakia, said 
that once Scandinavian states and Austria are admitted to the 
EU, "a long-term" need to expand the community eastwards would 
arise because union between West and East was the only guarantee 
of stability on the continent. 
  Asked by CTK whether Denmark preferred individual or joint 
entry of Central European countries into the EU, Petersen said 
the EU would apply the same model as in admitting the 
Scandinavian countries and Austria. The pattern is clear and 
logical: to conduct talks with each country separately, but 
simultaneously to the biggest measure possible, he stressed. 
  Petersen said that there were no problems in relations 
between Slovakia and Denmark, but added that trade was very low 
and cooperation other areas could also be promoted. Before 
Slovakia Petersen visited the Czech Republic. 

</TEXT>

