<F P=103> AU0205122394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava May 2 (CTK) -- Possibilities of economic 
cooperation were discussed today by Slovak Premier Jozef 
Moravcik, Foreign Minister Eduard Kukan and his Indonesian 
counterpart Ali Alatas. After the meeting, Moravcik said no 
problems existed between these two countries which would mar the 
promotion of cooperation. He said he also briefed his Indonesian 
partner on potential investments into Slovakia in view of access 
to third markets. 
  Alatas described the strengthening of economic relations as 
the aim of his two-day official visit to Slovakia which began 
yesterday. The conclusion of agreements in the future on the 
protection of investments and double-taxation could contribute 
to it, he added. Last year Slovakia exported to Indonesia 
machinery and chemical products amounting to 15 million USD, and 
imported from Indonesia tin, rubber and textiles worth 3.5 
million USD. 
  Alatas also met with Slovak Parliament Chairman Ivan 
Gasparovic and will be received by President Michal Kovac. 

