<H3> <TI>   Government Requesting $350-Million IMF Loan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Requesting $350-Million IMF Loan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94CH0232C Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Czech 29 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> 94CH0232C </F>
<F P=104>  Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Report by unnamed Bratislava correpondent: "Slovak Republic </F>
Wants $350 Million From IMF"] 
  [Text] Bratislava--The Slovak Government will try to obtain 
a so-called standby loan from the IMF in the amount of $350 
million, even though the restrictive measures in the form of the 
loan conditions will hit the public before the parliamentary 
elections in the fall and will obviously affect the prospects of 
the government parties. This was announced yesterday in 
Bratislava by Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik. The prime minister 
also confirmed that the condition for obtaining the IMF loan is 
to keep the deficit of the state budget under 4 percent of the 
GDP. 

</TEXT>

