<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade With Czech Republic Examined </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade With Czech Republic Examined </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0305121294 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 2 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU0305121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Trade With Czech Republic; We Import Food </F>
and Export Metallurgical and Engineering Products"] 
  [Text] Bratislava--In the first two months of this year, 
Slovakia achieved a surplus of 830 million korunas [Sk] in trade 
with the Czech Republic [CR]. This transpires from data the 
Slovak Statistical Office published in late April. According to 
this data, the CR remains Slovakia's key trading partner. 
Slovakia exports to the CR 37.6 percent of all of its total 
export volume and obtains from the CR 30.4 percent of its 
imports. Compared with the same period last year, Slovak 
exports to the CR declined 2.2 percent, while imports went up 
14.7 percent. 
  Apart from some food and agricultural products, such as 
cheese, wheat, corn, sweets, chocolate, bakery products, wine, 
and fruit juice, the CR purchases in Slovakia chiefly chemical 
products--mineral oils, gasoline, mineral fertilizers, paints 
and varnishes, herbicides, plastic goods, tires, and hides. 
Products of the consumer goods industry that the CR purchases in 
Slovakia include bathtubs, showers, washbasins, beef hides, 
wooden pallets and wood, combed and carded cotton, and all kinds 
of bottles, flasks, and demijohns. 
  Metallurgical, engineering, and electrical engineering 
products--rolled iron and steel products, wire, generators, 
pumps, excavators, bulldozers, lathes, forming machines, ball 
bearings, and tractors--represent an important part of Slovak 
exports to the CR. Important Slovak export commodities include, 
furthermore, refrigerators and freezers, washing machines, 
television sets, forklift trucks, and transformers. 
  Slovak imports consisted mainly of food--cream, fermented 
milk, yogurt, fats, sugar, salami and sausages, sweets, and 
bakery products. Slovakia imports from the CR, furthermore, 
coal, briquettes and coke, gasoline, mineral oils, 
pharmaceuticals, cosmetics, plastic products, rubber, tires, and 
newsprint. Dominant among engineering and metallurgical imports 
are intermediary and rolled iron and steel products, piston 
engines, turbines, pumps, industrial furnaces, and machinery for 
the food industry. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

