<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meksi Meets With Union Representatives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meksi Meets With Union Representatives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405175494 Tirana ATA in English 1006 GMT 4 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0405175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, May 4 (ATA) -- At the request of the Union 
of the Independent Trade Unions of Albania (UITUA), a meeting 
was held May 3 between the UITUA representatives and the 
government, headed by Premier Aleksander Meksi; the minister of 
labour, emigration and social assistance, Dashamir Shehu; the 
minister of mining and energy resources, Abdyl Xhaja; and other 
government members. The participants in the meeting agreed that 
the issuing of a law or agreement on indexation of inflation be 
sanctioned until the end of May also setting the deadline it 
will come to force. As regards privatization, by the end of 
May, the government promised to issue a decision which will also 
include the demands of the independent trade unions. They also 
agreed that the trade unions be familiarized with the procedures 
of preparing the vouchers and that legislation regarding this 
question be completed within the first six months to be 
submitted to the parliament for approval. 
  Mr. Meksi said that the price rise in the electric energy is 
an indispensability of the reform, but, taking into 
consideration the demands of the Independent Trade Unions for 
compensation for the electric energy, he will once again study 
the financial possibilities especially in the northeastern zone. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

