<H3> <TI>   FRY Envoy Protests Berisha Speech to Assembly </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FRY Envoy Protests Berisha Speech to Assembly </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405182894 Sofia BTA in English 1648 GMT 4 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0405182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, May 4 (BTA) -- Today the head of the 
Yugoslav diplomatic mission, Dr. Rados Smilkovic, made a protest 
before Deputy Foreign Minister Dimitur Ikonomov in connection 
with the recent speech delivered by Albanian President Sali 
Berisha at the Bulgarian parliament, the press office of the 
Embassy of Yugoslavia in Sofia announced. Mr. Berisha's speech 
is a violation of the basic rules of diplomacy, Dr. Smilkovic is 
cited as saying. Addressing parliament on April 28 this year 
during his official visit to Bulgaria, Mr. Berisha said that the 
war in Bosnia was a result of the decision of the communist 
dictatorship in Belgrade to establish Greater Serbia by 
aggression. 

</TEXT>

