<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   CTK Profiles New Attorney General </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CTK Profiles New Attorney General </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405191894 Prague CTK in English 1722 GMT 4 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0405191894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, May 4 (CTK) -- The Czech Government today 
unanimously approved Bohumira Kopecna in the post of the Czech 
attorney general. Previously -- from January 1, 1994 -- Kopecna 
was charged with temporary heading of the Attorney General's 
Office as deputy attorney general until the appointment of an 
attorney general. 
  Bohumira Kopecna, LLB, was born on July 28, 1946. She 
graduated at the Law School of Prague Charles University and in 
1971 she began to work at the District Prosecutor's Office in 
Bruntal, north Moravia. Later she worked at District 
Prosecutor's Office in Sumperk, north Moravia, and from 1975 she 
was prosecutor in the department of general crime at Municipal 
Prosecutor's Office in Brno, south Moravia. 
  In 1990, Kopecna was appointed deputy prosecutor at 
Brno-Countryside Prosecutor's Office, where she worked until 
April 1993. Then she returned to Brno Prosecutor's Office where 
she worked until December 1993, when the Czech Justice Minister 
Jiri Novak appointed her deputy attorney general. 
  Kopecna has never been member of a political party. "I am 
neither member of any party nor I do intend to join any party, 
but I favor the Civic Democratic Party (ODS). It is true, that 
I voted for them in the last (June 1992) elections," Kopecna 
told CTK on Tuesday. She also said that if she is proposed to 
the post of the attorney general, she would accept, also because 
it was unbearable to exercise simultaneously the functions of 
the attorney general and deputy attorney general. "It is 
necessary to separate these functions," she said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

