<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Havel Sees `Beginning' of Settlement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Havel Sees `Beginning' of Settlement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0505093594 Prague CTK in English 2001 GMT 4 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0505093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague May 4 (CTK) -- President Vaclav Havel 
welcomed today's signing of Palestine self-rule accord and said 
he considered it the beginning of Middle East settlement. He 
told Czech Television that former Czechoslovakia and later on 
the Czech Republic had always supported peaceful and just 
settlement of the situation in the region. This attitude has 
been evidenced by balanced relations with the two parties, Havel 
added. "The Czech Republic is undoubtedly ready to continue its 
assistance, especially regarding the reconstruction of the 
self-rule areas," Havel stressed. 

</TEXT>

