<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Christian Democrats Call For New Coalition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Christian Democrats Call For New Coalition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0505121694 Budapest MTI in English 2002 GMT 4 May 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0505121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 4 May (MTI) -- The Christian Democratic 
People's Party (KDNP) is the only political force in Hungary 
which relies on stable principles and is able to pursue a policy 
which encompasses both commitment to a market economy and social 
sensitivity, KDNP Chairman Laszlo Surjan said at a rally in 
Budapest today, closing his party's electoral campaign. 
  After the parliamentary elections, Hungary should continue 
to 
press on down the path it has followed over the past four years, 
Surjan said. Owing to its policy programme and team of experts, 
the KDNP is capable of giving a positive boost to the current 
government's work, he said, stressing that the present governing 
coalition should be transformed and refreshed rather than 
dismissed. 
  In Surjan's view, conservative Christian Democratic policy 
should play a determining role even in the future, because 
neither the liberal nor the socialist alternative can solve the 
country's current problems. 

</TEXT>

