<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Horn Seeks Democratic Left Victory </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Horn Seeks Democratic Left Victory </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0505075894 Budapest MTI in English 2018 GMT 4 May 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0505075894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 4 May (MTI) -- According to the 
experience of the Hungarian Socialist Party (MSZP), most 
Hungarians believe that the current government proved its 
incompetence over the past four years, and rewarded loyalty 
rather than expertise and skill, MSZP Chairman Gyula Horn told a 
rally in Tatabanya, western Hungary, today. Furthermore, due to 
their decreasing living standards, Hungarians would like May to 
be a month of change, Horn said. 
  Referring to recent harsh attacks on Horn, a journalist 
asked 
the MSZP Chairman whether he was considering giving up his 
political career. Horn replied: 
  "The support and encouragement I receive everywhere in the 
country lends me strength. The idea of giving up my political 
career because of a series of slanders has never occurred to me 
at all. All the more because I know that this is what they 
would like to achieve through these provocations. I do not 
cling on to any office, but over the past four years my primary 
goal was to bring the new, democratic, European left-wing to 
victory in Hungary," Horn said. 

</TEXT>

