<H3> <TI>   Boross Addresses Campaign Rally in Pecs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Boross Addresses Campaign Rally in Pecs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0505125294 Budapest MTI in English 2057 GMT 4 May 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0505125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 4 May (MTI) -- Although the government 
has committed errors over the past four years, Hungary has 
advanced so far that there is no way back to the former 
conditions, Prime Minister Peter Boross, prime minister 
candidate of the Hungarian Democratic Forum (MDF), the senior 
governing party, told a rally at Pecs tonight. 
  The prime minister pointed out that Hungary, which inherited 
a ruined economy, a disintegrated society and a fallen political 
regime, now has a viable system of democratic institutions, and 
an economy based on private property. Since no party 
cooperating with the trade unions has ever implemented a liberal 
economic programme, there is a suspicion that the Socialists do 
not want to implement it at all. 
  What is at stake in the elections is whether the country 
returns to the failed political regime or prevents the 
interruption of what has started -- even if with errors, 
difficulties and the problems of incompletion. "I trust in the 
instinctive wisdom of the Hungarian nation, which has never 
voted for the left of its own accord -- there had to be an army 
present," the prime minister said. 

</TEXT>

