<H3> <TI>   Jeszenszky Views Four Years of Foreign Policy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jeszenszky Views Four Years of Foreign Policy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405143394 Budapest MTI in English 1346 GMT 4 May 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0405143394 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 4 May (MTI) -- "Hungary's ship is heading 
for a safe port, and a good steersman knows everything not only 
about navigation but also of landing," Minister of Foreign 
Affairs Geza Jeszenszky said at an international press 
conference held by the management of the ministry on Wednesday. 
"The anchor is yet to be cast well but the present cabinet has 
already marked out a place for it," Jeszenszky continued, using 
this metaphor to summarize the results of the Hungarian 
Government's foreign policy over the past four years. 
  The minister said this policy has been successful, also 
according to foreign opinions. The government has carried 
through most of what it promised in this field at the time of 
taking office, he said. The cabinet's accomplishment is based 
on ideas and values professed by the bulk of the population. 
This has contributed to establishing the external preconditions 
of internal political and economic development, Jeszenszky said. 

</TEXT>

