<H3> <TI>   President, Cabinet Discuss State Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President, Cabinet Discuss State Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405154994 Warsaw PAP in English 1534 GMT 4 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0405154994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, May 4 -- President Lech Walesa attended a 
part of the Wednesdays Cabinet meeting devoted to state 
security. Discussed were proposals for legally regulating the 
Army command and issues related to the modification of Army 
structures, the presidential press bureau said Wednesday. 
  The president announced that positions agreed during the 
meeting would be presented to the Sejm, the communique says. 
Walesa said that the strikes of the strategic branches of the 
economy had a negative impact on state security, but he warned 
against forcing a temporary solutions on trade unions. 

</TEXT>

