<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Poland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sejm Speaker Criticizes Solidarity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sejm Speaker Criticizes Solidarity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405180894 Warsaw PAP in English 1727 GMT 4 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0405180894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, May 4 -- Sejm Speaker Jozef Oleksy 
criticized Solidarity's strivings to gain a dominant position in 
workers' representation during a meeting with the Warsaw-based 
FSO car plant on Wednesday. "I do not accept the union which 
has the overthrowing of the government as its aim," Oleksy said. 
"Solidarity's historical achievements are enormous but the 
proclamation of a general strike is a last resort all over the 
world. I do not think that the situation in the country 
justifies such a need," added the Sejm speaker. 
  According to Oleksy, workers' incomes will be ever more 
differentiated. "The thing is, though, not to forget about an 
elementary sense of social justice. The notion of social 
justice was rejected four years ago. This government is trying 
to implement a different strategy," stated Oleksy. 
  The Sejm speaker also said that four years ago FSO was 
condemned to destruction by some politicians. "Today it is a 
prosperous plant which has prospects for development. This 
proves that it is necessary to create own, Polish solutions 
instead of plagiarizing western solutions, which often do not 
correspond to the Polish reality," concluded the Sejm speaker. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

