<H3> <TI>   Sobotka Appointed Deputy Interior Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sobotka Appointed Deputy Interior Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505081794 Warsaw PAP in English 0743 GMT 5 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0505081794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, May 5 -- Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak, on 
the motion of the interior minister, appointed Zbigniew Sobotka 
undersecretary of state at the Interior Ministry as of May 4, 
the government press bureau has announced. 
  Zbigniew Sobotka, 42, is a metallurgist. He was a Sejm 
deputy of the first and second Sejm tenure and a member of the 
Sejm administration and internal affairs committee and the 
political advisory committee attached to the interior minister. 
  In the years 1986-1990 he was a member of the Central 
Committee of the Polish United Workers' Party (PZPR) and between 
1989 and 1990 he was a deputy member of the Political Bureau of 
the Central Committee of PZPR. He participated in the round 
table talks in 1989. Zbigniew Sobotka is a member of the main 
council of the Social Democracy of the Republic of Poland 
(SDRP). He is married, with three children. 

</TEXT>

