<H3> <TI>   Walesa Meets With U.S. Commerce Secretary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Walesa Meets With U.S. Commerce Secretary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505105994 Warsaw PAP in English 1024 GMT 5 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0505105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, May 5 -- President Lech Walesa received on 
Thursday U.S. Secretary of Commerce Ronald Brown in Warsaw for 
the East-West Economic Forum. 
  Greeting the guest Walesa said that Poland is trying to 
reform its economy. The process is difficult and the road from 
communism to capitalism is long, but there is no danger that 
Poland will veer from this direction. Walesa also said that he 
was counting on the fact that the United States will monitor the 
equality of partners. We do not want any special treatment, we 
want to be treated as partners emphasised Walesa. 
  Brown said that the dialogue between the east and west is of 
key importance to peace and development in the world. The 
United States is very supportive of the changes in Poland, said 
Brown adding that the U.S. and Poland are linked very closely 
and are co-dependent. 

</TEXT>

