<H3> <TI>   Walesa Receives Ukrainian General </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Walesa Receives Ukrainian General </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405213294 Warsaw PAP in English 2043 GMT 4 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0405213294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, May 4 -- President Lech Walesa received on 
Wednesday Chief of the General Staff of the Ukrainian Armed 
Forces, General Anatoliy Lopata, the presidential press office 
reported. 
  "Our countries have won independence and we do not have to 
fight there where our interests are not involved. The old 
threats have gone but new ones have emerged. We have to see 
that and build common future in the integrating Europe," 
President Walesa said greeting his guest in the Belweder 
presidential office. "There is no freedom when there is no free 
Ukraine. Without free Ukraine there can be no free Poland," 
Walesa stressed. 
  General Lopata conveyed to President Walesa greetings from 
the President of Ukraine, Leonid Kravchuk, stressing that he 
wanted good relations between the Polish and Ukrainian armed 
forces. The meeting was attended by Ukrainian Ambassador 
Gennadiy Udovenko and Chief of the General Staff of the Polish 
Armed Forces, General Tadeusz Wilecki. 

</TEXT>

