<H3> <TI>   Parliament Dismisses Television Council Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Dismisses Television Council Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0505120994 Prague CTK in English 2007 GMT 4 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0505120994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava May 4 (CTK) -- The Slovak parliament 
passed a motion dismissing all but two of the members of the 
Slovak Television Council today. Supporters of the government 
coalition's bill said the Council had sought to take over the 
running the channel whereas it was meant only to ensure its 
objectivity. The government was also concerned at the Council's 
pro-Meciar bias and preferred all parliamentary parties to be 
represented in it. The opposition decried the bill as an 
infringement of democracy and a purge. 
  The motion was passed only in a repeat vote because in the 
first attempt deputies had left a number of voting papers 
invalid. 
  Today's edition of the trade union daily PRACA commented 
that 
the present coalition would be interested in voting "its people" 
onto the Television Council because transmission times for party 
political broadcasts are at stake before the general elections, 
to be held September 30-October 1. 

</TEXT>

