<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Denies KNSB Charge of Phone Taps </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Denies KNSB Charge of Phone Taps </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0305172694 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0305172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Council of Ministers Press Center issued a 
statement today in connection with the statement that Professor 
Krustyu Petkov made today at a news conference of the KNSB 
[Confederation of Independent Trade Unions in Bulgaria] in which 
he claimed that the telephones of the trade unions that are 
preparing to conduct national protest actions on 4 May are 
tapped. The statement denies the KNSB claim. In its own 
announcement, the Interior Ministry Press Center points out such 
actions are not allowed, as they would violate the Law on 
Special Intelligence-Gathering Devices. 

</TEXT>

