<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Received by President Zhelev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Received by President Zhelev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405093794 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 0900 
GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0405093794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 4 May President Zhelyu Zhelev received 
Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali Alatas,, who is on an official 
visit to Bulgaria. Presidential Spokesman Valentin Stoyanov 
reports on the main topics discussed during the talk: 
  [Begin Stoyanov recording] There are no political 
differences between the two countries. This is a prerequisite 
for intensifying relations between the two countries, especially 
in the trade and economic sphere. We hope that this will be 
achieved. 
  President Zhelev asked Alatas to influence the Islamic 
Conference Organization to drop the Bulgarian Turks issue from 
its agenda. This issue has been on the organization's agenda 
for several years already. This is a a total anachronism, 
because the rights of the Bulgarian Turks have been fully 
restored. They are among the members of the parliament and in 
the organs of the municipal power, and it appears that the whole 
issue is now obsolete. 
  Alatas promised to raise the issue during the organization's 
next session in Tunisia, because, according to him, the 
organization has other more important issues that it must 
resolve. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

