<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alatas Supports Dividing Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alatas Supports Dividing Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405143594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1300 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0405143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] My visit was a result of very important and 
specific changes in both our countries, Indonesian Foreign 
Minister Ali Alatas said at a news conference today prior to his 
departure. He pointed out that in addition to developing trade 
and economic relations, the two countries must seek together 
third markets in their regions, the Balkans and the Far East. 
  Regarding the conflict in Bosnia-Herzegovina, the guest said 
that the ethnic basis of the conflict must not be ignored and 
that Indonesia supports dividing Bosnia-Herzegovina into three 
ethnic parts -- provided it is done in a just way and in 
accordance with the country's independence. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

