<H3> <TI>   Vacaroiu, Chinese Military Group Discuss Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vacaroiu, Chinese Military Group Discuss Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405191794 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1700 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0405191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Romanian Prime Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu received 
this evening a Chinese military delegation led by Colonel 
General Zhang Wannian, member of the Central Military Commission 
and chief of staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, who 
is visiting our country on the invitation of the Romanian 
Ministry of National Defense. The meeting was attended by 
Lieutenant General Dumitru Cioflina, chief of staff of the 
Romanian Army. 
  After conveying to the Romanian prime minister greetings 
from 
his counterpart, the guest expressed satisfaction that the good 
Romanian-Chinese relations, unaltered by the changes that have 
taken place in international life, continue to develop in the 
spirit of the old traditions that bind us. 
  The visit of the delegation that he is leading, through its 
very rich program and through the various exchanges of opinions 
that it occasions, makes a contribution to a better 
familiarization of the sides with each other and to the 
enhancement of relations of cooperation between the two armies 
and two countries. 
  The prime minister assured the Chinese guest that the 
Romanian people follow with keen interest China's outstanding 
achievements on the road to economic reform in the past 15 years 
and also assured him that this country, with its huge potential, 
represents one of the current foreign political guide marks of 
Romania. 
  As a continuation of bilateral contacts in the past months, 
the visit to Romania of Li Peng, premier of the State Council of 
the People's Republic of China, scheduled for summer 1994, is 
expected with great interest, reads a press release faxed to us 
by a spokesman for the government. 

</TEXT>

