<F P=102>   AU0505110594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0505110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Excerpt] The joint aggressors have not stopped attacking 
the Bihac region. Karadzic's chetniks last night stepped up 
artillery attacks on the defenders of the Grabez part of the 
front and the Ggrmusko-Srbljanski plateau. They also started 
shelling the suburbs and central part of Cazin at 2300. They 
fired some 20 mortar and howitzer shells. 
  There was also some shelling on the Bosanska Krupa and Buzim 
front. Anti-aircraft weapons and heavy machine guns are being 
used constantly. The paramilitary formations of the Kladusa 
traitors and rebels have stepped attacks last night and this 
morning. They are attacking Trzac, Liskovac, Krivaja, and 
Pecigrad in the Cazin commune, and Todorovo and Varoska Rijeka 
with 82 mm and 120 mm mortars and guns. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

