<H3> <TI>   Serb-UN Talks Begin on UN Deployment in Brcko </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb-UN Talks Begin on UN Deployment in Brcko </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505105694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1001 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0505105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brcko, 5 May (TANJUG) -- Talks began in Brcko this 
afternoon on the deployment of UN observers in the region. The 
UN Protection Forces [UNPROFOR] delegation to the talks is 
headed by Sergio de Melo, an assistant to Yasushi Akashi, and 
the Serb delegation by Dr. Nikola Koljevic, deputy president of 
the Serb Republic, and Major General Novica Simic, commander of 
the East Bosnia corps. The talks are also being attended by 
Miodrag Pajic, president of the Brcko municipal assembly, and by 
Milenko Vojinovic, deputy in the assembly of the republic of 
Srpska. Following the talks, the UNPROFOR delergation is 
expected to tour the confrontation lines and sectors of the 
frontlines. It is planned that the UNPROFOR delegation will 
visit the hospital in Brcko, the Interplet enterprise, and some 
parts of the town. 

</TEXT>

