<H3> <TI>   Belgrade Protests Berisha Speech in Sofia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Belgrade Protests Berisha Speech in Sofia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405164094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1558 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, 4 May (TANJUG) -- Rados Smiljkovic, the 
ambassador of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia in Sofia [name 
and title as received], today lodged a protest with the 
Bulgarian Foreign Ministry in reaction to a speech delivered by 
Albanian President Sali Berisha in the Bulgarian National 
Assembly when he attacked the FRY, Serbia, and the Serbian 
people in the harshest of terms. Such an anti-Serbian attitude 
displayed by the Albanian president raises the issue of 
responsibility borne by the hosts for this verbal assault on the 
FRY in the highest institution of Bulgarian democracy, the 
protest underlines. 
  We express our deepest regret at the fact that such a 
possibility was granted to a man well known for his advocacy of 
the war option in the Balkans, a man who is voluntarily offering 
everybody -- primarily Turkey -- bases and strongholds for 
military operations against the FRY, it is said in the protest. 
  The Albanian president is disseminating lies about the 
creation of a Greater Serbia in order to conceal his own program 
for the creation of a Greater Albania, which, besides Kosmet 
[Kosovo and Metohija], would include western Macedonia [The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] and parts of 
Montenegro. According to the protest, the most glaring untruths 
in Berisha's speech in the Bulgarian Assembly related to Kosmet, 
because, it is said, the Albanian population there neither 
numbers two million nor has their autonomy been abolished. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

