<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   HZDS Protests Austrian Election `Interference' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    HZDS Protests Austrian Election `Interference' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405152294 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 30 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU0405152294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Allegedly Mendacious Defamations"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--Referring to the Slovak press, the 
Austrian APA agency yesterday reported that Anna Nagyova, former 
director of the Slovak prime minister's secretariat, was 
expecting a baby by former Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar. In 
addition to this information, the APA report also contains 
several invectives regarding their "supposedly not merely 
official business relations" and marital problems in both 
families. A statement made available to TA SR yesterday by 
Ondrej Hanko, spokesman for the Movement for a Democratic 
Slovakia [HZDS], notes in this context that, "by its vulgar, 
unsubstantiated, and mendacious contents, the APA report defames 
HZDS Chairman Vladimir Meciar and Anna Nagyova, head of his 
secretariat." In the name of the HZDS, Hanko openly asked 
Austrian President Thomas Klestil, Chancellor Franz Vranitzky, 
and Parliament Chairman Heinz Fischer how they assess the fact 
that, "before the early elections, Austrian media are 
interfering grossly and in the dirtiest possible way in the 
election campaign by their unfounded scandalization of a leading 
politician, the chairman of the largest political entity in 
neighboring Slovakia." He asks whether this does not constitute 
interference in the internal affairs of a neighboring country 
and in the hitherto exemplary friendly relations, which have 
been successfully developed by Meciar personally. HZDS 
representatives also sent a similar statement to leading 
Austrian dailies. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

