<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Report on 1993 Currency Development Approved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Report on 1993 Currency Development Approved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405190094 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1630 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1630 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The bank council of the National Bank of Slovakia 
discussed and approved today a report on 1993 currency 
development in Slovakia. The council has authorized Vladimir 
Masar, the bank's governor, to submit the report to the National 
Council. The bank council has stated that the priorities of the 
currency program have been successfully carried out, the price 
increases were kept at a minimum, and the internal 
convertibility of the Slovak koruna was maintained. The current 
account for the balance of payments ended in 1993 with a 
negative balance of $559 million, while the overall balance 
ended in a positive balance of $58.5 million. 

</TEXT>

