<H3> <TI>   Iliescu Congratulates Middle East Leaders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iliescu Congratulates Middle East Leaders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405200794 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1700 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0405200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Ion Iliescu today sent separate telegrams 
to Yasir 'Arafat, chairman of the PLO Executive Committee and 
president of the State of Palestine, Israeli Prime Minister 
Yitzhaq Rabin, and Israeli Foreign Affairs Minister Shim'on 
Peres, in which he congratulated them on the occasion of signing 
the accord on autonomy in Gaza and Jericho, an act to whose 
finalization, the cable reads, the recent talks held in 
Bucharest between the Palestinian leader and the Israeli foreign 
minister also made a contribution. 
  President Iliescu reasserts Romania's wish to continue to 
contribute to the achievement of favorable conditions for a just 
and durable peace in the Middle East. 
  In another telegram sent to Husni Mubarak, president of the 
Arab Republic of Egypt, President Iliescu voices his 
appreciation for the steady actions made by Egypt and its 
president to achieve peace in the Middle East region. President 
Iliescu also expresses the belief that Romanian-Egyptian 
relations will continue to develop to the mutual benefit of both 
countries. 

</TEXT>

