<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Railway Workers Join Strike in Silesia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Railway Workers Join Strike in Silesia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505090094 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0800 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0505090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Strikes in the Silesia region are spreading. 
The Solidarity Slasko-Dabrowski regional chairman said today 
that railway workers have joined the strike. Strikes began this 
morning at Bytom, Radzionkow, Brynow, Lisow, Kochanowice, Herby 
Stare, and Krupski Mlyn stations. Railway workers from 
Lubliniec joined the strike at 0700. The strikers have stopped 
servicing cargo trains and train engines, a communique says. 
The length of the strike depends on a decision of the 
Solidarity national strike headquarters. Railway workers have 
presented a list of demands that are similar to the trade 
union's national demands. [passage omitted] 
  Miners are also on strike. According to trade unionists, the 
strike continues in 22 hard-coal mines. The State Hard Coal 
Agency in Katowice confirmed that coal is not being mined in 20 
collieries. Miners from three zinc and lead mines are also on 
strike. 

</TEXT>

