<H3> <TI>   UNPROFOR To Stop Serbian Tanks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNPROFOR To Stop Serbian Tanks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0605111794 Paris AFP in English 1106 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0605111794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, May 6 -- The United Nations Protection 
Force (UNPROFOR) will stop two Serb tanks from crossing the 
military exclusion zone around Sarajevo Friday, UNPROFOR 
announced. The transit of the tanks -- the last of a total 
seven scheduled to cross the zone between 2:00 p.m. and 3:00 
p.m. (1200 and 1300 GMT) -- had been announced earlier Friday by 
a UNPROFOR spokesman. But a military UNPROFOR spokesman who 
refused to be identified said orders were given by the Bosnia 
UNPROFOR command to block the tanks. 

</TEXT>

