<H3> <TI>   Serbian Council Denounces Karadzic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Council Denounces Karadzic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0505191194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0505191194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The latest expulsion of the non-Serb population 
from Banja Luka and other Krajina municipalities is yet another 
illustration of the brutality and the insanity of the policy of 
violence conducted by war criminal Karadzic and his followers. 
This is contained in a statement issued today by the Serbian 
Citizens' Council. At their assembly held on 27 March of this 
year, citizens of Serbian nationality and Serbian ethnic origin 
again sent a clear message to the international community, 
explaining that the theory of the impossibility of coexistence 
in fact conceals the aggressor's aspirations to occupy territory 
and expel Bosniak Muslims from their homes. 
  For this reason we demand from all those responsible 
international subjects that can influence the course of solving 
the bloody Bosnia-Herzegovina drama to prevent further 
expulsions of Muslims and Croats from their homes, and to create 
the conditions for a speedy return of refugees and displaced 
people. This, in our view, is the precondition for peace in 
this region, reads the statement by the Serbian Citizens' 
Council. 

</TEXT>

