<H3> <TI>   Comments on No-Confidence Debate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Comments on No-Confidence Debate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505140694 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1000 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0505140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1000 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister Roman Kovac regards the 
deputies' proposal to express no confidence in himself as a kind 
of lesson. In an interview granted to the TASR news agency, he 
said that he learned from circles close to the Movement for a 
Democratic Slovakia [HZDS] that proposals similar to this one 
are being prepared to be raised at the next meeting of 
parliament. 
  Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik said the debate on no 
confidence in Roman Kovac documented the poverty of the 
political culture of certain sections of deputies and political 
groups. At the same time, he did not rule out that similar 
proposals on no confidence will appear in the future, too. He 
said, however, that he is convinced that these moves do not at 
all affect the stability of the present government. 

</TEXT>

