<F P=102>   AU0505160394 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1300 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0505160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Since the situation that would emerge if the 
anticipated cabinet changes are approved actually means a new 
mandate, we must accomplish within 50 days what we could not do 
in 16 months, otherwise we will fail miserably. This position 
was defended at a cabinet meeting today by Finance Minister 
Stoyan Aleksandrov. He later explained his motives at a news 
conference. 
  According to Stoyan Aleksandrov, if the government succumbs 
to trade union and political pressure and adopts a cheap, 
populist policy of compensations, a catastrophe will immediately 
follow. 
  At a meeting with Prime Minister Berov Finance Minister, 
Aleksandrov said it is not normal to divide the functions of the 
Finance Ministry leader's important post. 
  At the cabinet meeting today, the prime minister asked all 
the ministers to present by tomorrow morning at the latest 
written opinions on possible measures in their separate 
ministries by the end of June. 

