<H3> <TI>   Fidesz Urges Prevention of New `Broker Scandals' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fidesz Urges Prevention of New `Broker Scandals' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94CH0198D Budapest MAGYAR NEMZET in Hungarian 4 Mar 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> 94CH0198D </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MAGYAR NEMZET </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "New Broker Scandals Must Be </F>
Avoided"] 
  [Text] "The utilization of the surplus of financial 
institutions must be regulated, and this has been made 
especially timely by the case of the Lupis Brokerage," Lajos 
Kosa, parliamentary representative for Fidesz [Federation of 
Young Democrats] said. In this case, the state, and indirectly 
the citizens, suffered a loss. But this was not the first such 
scandal, because when the Ybl Bank went bankrupt, almost 2 
million forints from budgetary institutions were lost. 
  In the opinion of Fidesz, the financing of the institutions 
cannot be regulated in such a way that they would have no 
surplus at all from time to time. But if they do have a surplus, 
it is expedient to invest it, and in such a way that the money 
would be in the safest possible place. In the opinion of Fidesz 
it would be desirable for budgetary institutions to invest only 
in treasury bonds and other government bonds. 

</TEXT>

