<H3> <TI>   Strikes Continuing; Negotiations Stalled </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Strikes Continuing; Negotiations Stalled </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Solidarity `Ultimatum' </H4>

<F P=102> LD0505114794 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1024 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505114794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 5 May--In a telephone conversation with a 
reporter from Polish Radio Three on Thursday, Zygmunt Wrzodak, 
head of Solidarity in the Ursus tractor factory, said that one 
should not hold talks with the present government but should 
form strong structures attached to the Solidarity National 
Commission, which will form an interim government in the future. 
  "The government has to be given an ultimatum: If it wants to 
talk, then it should sit at the table and negotiate and fix some 
dates for things to be solved. If not, then we have to remove 
those people from the government and replace this government 
with an interim one," he said. 
  According to Wrzodak, this is the opinion of a few people 
from factory commissions in Mazowsze region, but the Solidarity 
National Commission should make a decision. In his opinion, all 
strikes should be clearly and properly coordinated. 

</TEXT>

