<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Election Results, Reactions Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    MIEP Leader Sees SZDSZ Victory </H4>

<F P=102> LD0905040494 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
0115 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0905040494 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Istvan Csurka, cochairman of the Hungarian </F>
Justice and Life Party, by correspondent Peter Obersovszky; date 
and place not given--recorded] 
  [Text] [Obsersovszky] In light of the figures, can you 
imagine a demonstration like the one you spoke about shortly 
before the elections? You spoke about 100,000 people and that 
the pronation parties, political groupings, and people ought to 
demonstrate that they did not want a left-wing victory. 
  [Csurka] This is the third time I have been asked a question 
like this this evening, as if there were a secret service here 
wanting to know what I am planning, and whether I am taking the 
Hungarian people to the streets. That is not my intention. I 
know what we must do. We must organize anew the Hungarian Way 
and the Hungarian Justice and Life Party [MIEP] on a 
professional basis. We have not had the money or financial 
resources for this so far. It will become clear now upon whom we 
can count. 
  Do not expect me to tell the Alliance of Free Democrats 
[SZDSZ], which has really come to power, what I plan. What I 
will say is that this victory is not the victory of the 
Hungarian Socialist Party, but the victory of the SZDSZ, because 
this government will be directed by the SZDSZ and it will 
function in accordance with the interests stipulated by the 
foreign supporters of the SZDSZ. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

