<H3> <TI>   MDF Proposes Coalition With FKGP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MDF Proposes Coalition With FKGP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0905085394 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
0800 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0905085394 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] One of the leaders of the Hungarian Democratic Forum 
[MDF] believes that her party can improve its election results 
if it forms a coalition with the other two conservative parties 
and they renounce their votes in favor of the MDF. Speaking on 
television's "Sunrise" [Napkelte] program, Krisztina Dobos said 
they are now beginning to hold talks about this with the 
Independent Smallholders Party [FKGP]. [FKGP Chairman] Jozsef 
Torgyan does not consider such an agreement to be impossible. 
According to the Smallholder chairman, as a matter of fact, 
differences so far have been between the party leaderships not 
the membership. 
  Bela Csepe, outgoing leader of the Christian Democrats 
parliamentary group, said that if necessary the Christian 
Democrats will step back in favor of the MDF. 

</TEXT>

