<HT>    "dreeu089_h_94018" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-089 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  9 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   FKGP, Fidesz Chairmen on Results </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FKGP, Fidesz Chairmen on Results </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0905093094 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
0800 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0905093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Jozsef Torgyan, chairman of the Independent 
Smallholders Party [FKGP], considers his party's role in the 
elections to have been successful. According to him, the 
Smallholders could become the most significant opposition force 
because, he said, after the Hungarian Democratic Forum's bad 
performance, there is still an internal explosion awaiting it. 
Torgyan also said that the Hungarian Socialist Party's success 
has to be accepted. 
  Viktor Orban, chairman of the Federation of Young Democrats 
[Fidesz] is of the view that in the past four years his party 
has traveled the path that it set itself in 1990. According to 
him, this was sufficient for it to achieve its election result. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

