<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Republic Party Reacts to Vote Result </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Republic Party Reacts to Vote Result </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0905135394 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1000 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0905135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Republic Party was one of the parties which have 
already commented on the election results. Katalin Horvath 
reports: 
  [Horvath] According to Republic Party Chairman Janos 
Palotas, 
people voted for parties rather than personalities. The 
sweeping victory of the Hungarian Socialist Party [MSZP] was due 
to this fact and it is the Hungarian Democratic Forum's 
government policy -- not the MSZP -- which is responsible for 
this. It is certain that these election results are not 
politically healthy, Janos Palotas said. This kind of victory 
is unprecedented even in the western democracies. But the MSZP 
won in democratic elections and the will of society should be 
respected. 
  As far as the economic policy programs of the MSZP and the 
Alliance of Free Democrats [SZDSZ] are concerned, they are 
similar to the Republic Party's economic ideas in many points, 
although they can only be compared when the MSZP and the SZDSZ 
present their ideas on domestic market regulation, taxes, 
customs duties, and inflation. 
  Janos Palotas hopes that the MSZP's victory does not cause a 
political shock and does not make the economy collapse. As far 
as the Republic Party is concerned, in Janos Palotas's view the 
party is ready for parliamentary work and it can enter 
parliament in the next elections. The Republic Party is now 
preparing for the local government elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

