to conclude an all-embracing election alliance with any party 
for the second round, he said, recalling the bad experiences of 
the second round of the 1990 elections. 
  However, Jozsef Torgyan did not exclude the possibility of 
concluding one-off agreements with the parties on the national 
side, or that they might step back in favor of one another. 
  Mrs. G. Nagy, nee Agnes Maczo [FKGP deputy chairwoman], said 
she can imagine this at most in connection with the Christian 
