<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Andras Kerekes] </F>
  [Excerpts] The outcome of 127 mandates has been decided in 
the first round of the elections. [passage omitted] In the 
first round 68.9 percent of the electorate voted. A news 
conference for the international press ended not long ago at the 
National Election Center, where they primarily wanted to inform 
the foreign journalists about the overall preliminary results. 
[passage omitted] 
  They have now also announced the distribution of seats on 
the 
regional party lists. According to this, the Hungarian 
Socialist Party [MSZP] will receive another 53 seats, with 32.9 
percent of the votes; the Alliance of Free Democrats [SZDSZ] has 
28 seats with 19.7 percent; the Hungarian Democratic Forum [MDF] 
has 18 seats with 11.7 percent; the Independent Smallholders 
Party [FKGP] has 14 seats with not quite 9 percent of the votes; 
and the Christian Democrats [KDNP] -- although they gained a few 
votes more than Fidesz [Federation of Young Democrats] -- the 
latter received seven seats but the KDNP received only five. 
This is because of the different numbers of voters in the 
regions. 
  A total of 27 seats passed from the regional lists to the 
national lists [to be decided in the second round]. 
  Zoltan Toth, head of the national election office, said that 
of approximately 22,000 ballot papers they are unable to account 
for a total of 18, but they hope that by 1500 this afternoon, 
the time of the briefing in parliament, the premliminary results 
of the first round will be complete including these. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

